newsitem.title: DUBAI: One, three month Saudi t-bills up, six month down.
newsitem.headline: One, three month Saudi t-bills up, six month down.

text.p: Yields on one and three month Saudi treasury bills climbed and those on six-month bills fell at this week's Saudi Arabian Monetary Agency offering worth three billion riyals, a banker said on Monday.
The yield on 28-day bills rose to 5.3331 percent from 5.2952 and the rate on the 91-day paper climbed to 5.4439 percent from 5.4201. The rate on 182-day bills was 5.5035 from 5.5444.
One month, three month and six month interbank rates were steady at 5-7/16, 5/16 percent, and 5-9/16, 7/16 and 5-11/16, 9/16 respectively.
